TITLE: Typia LLM Application Violation Example
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates an example of using `typia.llm.application` with a class (`BbsArticleController`) that violates the required constraints, resulting in a compilation error. The example defines an interface `BbsArticleController` with `create` and `erase` methods. The attempt to create an `ILlmApplication` using `typia.llm.application` triggers TypeScript errors due to the return type of `create` being a union with undefined, and the parameter type of `erase` not being a single object.
